description:
Vacancy: Administrator / Receptionist at the Premium Fitness Club Royal Boxing \\& Fitness (Palm Jumeirah, Dubai)

Royal Boxing \\& Fitness is looking for a friendly, organized, and responsible front desk administrator who will become the face of our club and maintain a high level of service for our premium clients.

Requirements:

– 2–3 years of experience in sales or customer service within the premium segment (fitness clubs, luxury hotels, boutiques, spas, etc.);

– Confident use of CRM systems, basic knowledge of Excel and Word;

– Excellent communication skills, clear and polite speech, strong attention to detail, and client\\-focused mindset;

– Well\\-groomed and professional appearance;

– Fluent in Russian and English (spoken communication is a must);

– Arabic language is a plus, but not required.

Responsibilities:

– Welcoming and assisting guests at the club;

– Working with the CRM system: client bookings, schedule management, attendance tracking;

– Maintaining and updating the client database;

– Actively selling memberships and all additional club services (massage, cryotherapy, personal training, etc.);

– Coordinating with trainers, massage therapists, and the marketing team;

– Maintaining a premium\\-level atmosphere and order at the front desk.

Conditions:

– Work schedule: 6 days per week (6/1\\);

– Salary: 6000 AED base \\+ commission from all club service sales;

– Work in one of the most stylish fitness clubs in Dubai — Palm Jumeirah;

– Supportive management, international team, and a comfortable working environment;

– Real opportunity for career growth within the brand.

Job Type: Full\\-time

Pay: AED6,000\\.00 per month

Language:

* Russian (Preferred)

This is an internship program, and it is customized for University students who have completed at least four (4\\) years of studies and are passionate about Sustainability and the Environment topics.  



It also requires a high level of trust, professionalism and communication.

**Company:**


Alpin Limited is a leading sustainability consultant in the Middle East, with its global headquarters in Masdar City, Abu Dhabi—the world's first sustainable city. We're on a mission to transform the built environment by providing innovative commissioning, sustainability, and climate change solutions. As a company, we are committed to thought leadership and making a tangible difference in the world. We pride ourselves on having a diverse, multicultural team of experts who are passionate about creating a more sustainable future. At Alpin, you'll be part of a dynamic, "young\\-at\\-heart" culture that values collaboration, innovation, and continuous learning.


To know more about Alpin Limited and its services and projects please visit www.alpinme.com

 **Reports Directly to:**



Sustainability Manager

 **Roles and Responsibilities:**



* Member of Sustainability team;
* Development of reports;
* Support in development of Presentations;
* Understand and implement the principles of project management (scheduling, resource leveling, effective meetings, client relations);
* Site and Office Based Consultancy;
* Support in the green building design and LEED/BREEAM documentation process, as well as project specifications, calculations, plans and submittals for LEED/BREEAM compliance;
* Coordinate with/support contractors including MEP and civil engineers;
* Conduct product and technology research related to sustainability;
* Personal development and plan to develop skills necessary to become a full member of the Alpin team

**HSE Roles, Responsibilities and Accountability:**

* In addition to your responsibility towards following ALPIN’s Integrated Management System, every employee at ALPIN is required to familiarize themselves with ALPIN’s Environmental Impact Assessment and contribute towards minimizing their individual environmental impact in the course of their work.
* It is the duty of all employees to act within the legal responsibilities imposed upon them and the Company’s Quality, Environment and Health \\& Safety policies. All employees must familiarize themselves with the Company’s Integrated Management System’s policies and procedures

**Skills:**

* Strong interpersonal skills and ability to work with both clients and consultants;
* Knowledge of current sustainability standards and practices;
* Knowledge of current sustainability standards: LEED, BREEAM;
* Working towards at least one of the accreditations: LEED GA or AP, PQP
* Fluent written \\& spoken in English;
* Strong communication skills (Written, electronic \\& spoken)
* Bachelor’s Degree (or close to completion of one) in related discipline (Environmental, Construction Management, Engineering or Architecture);
* Excellent planning and organization skills required for our fast‐paced environment;
* Ability to self‐manage;

**Additional Experience/Certifications:**

* Hands‐on engineering and project management skills
* UAE Driving license \\& personal mode of transportation; must be resident in Dubai, UAE.

**Learning Outcomes:**


The successful applicant will gain the following learning outcomes form this position:

* Deepening of awareness in local, regional and global environmental issues, and the role that the construction sector plays in contributing to these issues;
* Hands on experience of both design and construction projects;
* Development of analytical and research skills;
* Experience of the dynamics of a fast‐paced consultancy environment;
